Adult male.description: The breeding male Brewer's Blackbird is glossier, with a stronger purplish cast on the head and breast not seen on the Rusty Blackbird. In fall and winter, male Brewer's show less rusty feather edging than the Rusty Blackbird.

Female.description: Female Brewer's Blackbirds have dark eyes and are brownish gray rather than rusty brown like Rusty Blackbirds. Beware, female Brewer's occasionally have pale eyes.

Adult male.description: Common Grackles are larger overall with a thicker bill and a longer, wedge-shaped tail than Rusty Blackbirds, which have a square-tipped tail and are more slender overall.

Female.description: Common Grackles are larger with a longer wedge-shaped tail unlike the shorter square-tipped tail of Rusty Blackbirds. Females are dark brown overall and lack the rusty color of female Rusty Blackbirds.

Breeding male (Red-winged).description: Red-winged Blackbirds are more compact that Rusty Blackbirds. They also have dark eyes, shorter and stouter bills, and shorter tails.

Female (Red-winged).description: Red-winged Blackbirds are smaller and more compact than Rusty Blackbirds. Females are heavily streaked overall unlike female Rusty Blackbirds, which are mostly unstreaked with rusty feather edges.

Adult male.description: Brown-headed Cowbird are more compact than Rusty Blackbirds with dark eyes, shorter and stouter bills, and shorter tails.
